    "body": "Note that is the way it works with one col:\n\n```\nIn [19]: df.sort(\"a\")\nOut[19]:\n    a   b\n0   1   9\n3   1   2\n1   2 NaN\n6   4   5\n4   6   5\n5   8   4\n2 NaN   5\n```\n\nAlso Series `order` method (pretty much the same as sort) offers na_last argument:\n\n```\nna_last : boolean (optional, default=True)\n    Put NaN's at beginning or end\n```\n"
